comments.body:
@eliotjordan thank you for catching that! I thought I had tested that case but it was definitely broken.

I don't see the button alignment issue and I didn't change any templates or css, so I'm not sure what's going on there.

This is ready for another review.

So maybe the context becomes:

```
  "@context": [
    "https://bibdata.princeton.edu/context.json",
    {
      "geojson": "https://purl.org/geojson/vocab#",
      "coverage_point": {
        "@container": "@list",
        "@id": "geojson:coordinates"
      }
  }],
```

Unless we want to add `coverage_point` to the bibdata context doc.
